## 7. Using `hue`

`hue` uses another variable to divide observations into groups.

```python
sns.scatterplot(
    data=students,
    x="study_hours",
    y="exam_score",
    hue="course",
)
```

Now every course receives a separate visual category.

```text
Python students
AI students
Data Science students
```

Complete example:

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns


figure, axis = plt.subplots(
    figsize=(8, 5)
)

sns.scatterplot(
    data=students,
    x="study_hours",
    y="exam_score",
    hue="course",
    ax=axis,
)

axis.set_title(
    "Study Hours and Scores by Course"
)

axis.set_xlabel("Study Hours")
axis.set_ylabel("Exam Score")

plt.show()
```

`hue` is useful for comparing multiple groups without creating separate charts.

