## 9. Line Plot

A line plot displays change across an ordered variable.

Suppose we have model-training data:

```python
training_history = pd.DataFrame(
    {
        "epoch": [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6],
        "training_loss": [
            0.92,
            0.70,
            0.54,
            0.41,
            0.31,
            0.24,
        ],
        "validation_loss": [
            0.95,
            0.74,
            0.59,
            0.50,
            0.52,
            0.60,
        ],
    }
)
```

Create a line chart:

```python
figure, axis = plt.subplots(
    figsize=(8, 5)
)

sns.lineplot(
    data=training_history,
    x="epoch",
    y="training_loss",
    label="Training Loss",
    ax=axis,
)

sns.lineplot(
    data=training_history,
    x="epoch",
    y="validation_loss",
    label="Validation Loss",
    ax=axis,
)

axis.set_title("Model Training History")
axis.set_xlabel("Epoch")
axis.set_ylabel("Loss")

plt.show()
```

The validation loss starts increasing after epoch 4, while training loss keeps decreasing.

This may indicate overfitting.

