## 16. Box Plot Components

```text
       possible outlier
              *
              |
        upper whisker
              |
        +-----------+
        |     Q3    |
        |-----------| ← Median
        |     Q1    |
        +-----------+
              |
        lower whisker
```

A box plot commonly displays:

* Median
* First quartile
* Third quartile
* Interquartile range
* Whiskers
* Potential outliers

---

## 17. Mathematical Intuition: Quartiles

Given sorted scores:

```text
45, 52, 58, 65, 72, 78, 81, 86, 94, 97
```

The median divides the dataset into two halves.

The quartiles divide the values into four sections:

```text
Q1 → 25th percentile
Q2 → 50th percentile or median
Q3 → 75th percentile
```

The interquartile range is:

[
IQR = Q3 - Q1
]

A common outlier rule is:

[
\text{Lower boundary}
=====================

Q1 - 1.5(IQR)
]

[
\text{Upper boundary}
=====================

Q3 + 1.5(IQR)
]

Values outside these boundaries may be displayed as potential outliers.

They should not automatically be deleted. They may be genuine observations.

