## 30. Important Code Explanation

```python
sns.histplot(
    data=data,
    x="exam_score",
    bins=6,
    kde=True,
    ax=axis,
)
```

* `data=data` provides the DataFrame.
* `x="exam_score"` selects the column.
* `bins=6` creates six intervals.
* `kde=True` adds an estimated density curve.
* `ax=axis` draws on the supplied Matplotlib axis.

```python
sns.scatterplot(
    data=data,
    x="study_hours",
    y="exam_score",
    hue="course",
    style="gender",
    ax=axis,
)
```

* `x` controls horizontal position.
* `y` controls vertical position.
* `hue` separates course groups.
* `style` separates gender groups.

```python
correlation_matrix = numerical_data.corr()
```

Calculates pairwise correlations between numerical columns.

```python
sns.heatmap(
    correlation_matrix,
    annot=True,
    fmt=".2f",
    ax=axis,
)
```

* `annot=True` prints each correlation value.
* `fmt=".2f"` displays two decimal places.

```python
plt.close(figure)
```

Releases the figure after saving it.

