## 38. Summary

* Seaborn provides high-level statistical visualizations.
* It works closely with Pandas and builds on Matplotlib.
* Scatter plots show numerical relationships.
* `hue` introduces an additional grouping variable.
* Line plots show change across an ordered variable.
* Bar plots summarize numerical values by category.
* Count plots show category frequencies.
* Histograms show numerical distributions.
* Box plots summarize quartiles and potential outliers.
* Violin plots show estimated distribution shapes.
* Strip and swarm plots display individual observations.
* Correlation measures linear relationships.
* Heatmaps visualize matrix values.
* Pair plots compare several numerical variables.
* Figure-level functions create their own figures.
* Axes-level functions can draw on supplied Matplotlib axes.
* Statistical charts must be interpreted in the context of data quality and sample size.

